{"id": 231947280, "title": "NILDS: Nigerians no longer require foreign legislative training &#8211; Akpabio", "text": "The President of the Senate, Godswill Akpabio, says Nigerians no longer need to travel abroad for legislative training given the standard of facilities and professionals at the National Institute for Legislative and Democratic Studies (NILDS). Mr Akpabio, who said this when he visited the institute on Friday in Abuja, described the institute as \u201cNigeria\u2019s Cambridge and Harvard Universities.\u201d \u201cWith this infrastructure, Nigerians no longer need to travel overseas for legislative training; this is our own Cambridge and Harvard,\u201d Mr Akpabio said. Meanwhile, the Director-General of NILDS, Abubakar Sulaiman, unveiled NILDS\u2019s latest publication,\u201d25 Years of Democracy and Development in Nigeria.\u201d during the Senate President\u2019s visit. The publication, which features a foreword by Mr Akpabio, chronicles Nigeria\u2019s democratic journey and development since 1999. Nigeria returned to democratic governance in 1999 after several years of military rule. READ ALSO: What can be done to ensure orderliness, security in parliament \u2013 NILDS DG From 1999 to date, the country has experienced 25 years of democracy without a break. Accompanied by the Senate Leader, Opeyemi Bamidele; Osita Ngwu, Asuquo Ekpenyong, Abiru Adetokunbo, Mr Akpabio commended the efforts of the management of the institute In a similar development, the Speaker of the ECOWAS Parliament, Maimounatou Ibrahima, has sought NILDS\u2019 assistance in the area of capacity development of parliamentarians and their support staff during a visit to the institute. The DG of the institute, Mr Sulaiman, a professor, assured the Institute\u2019s readiness to provide its services to the ECOWAS Parliament, emphasising the institute\u2019s commitment to advancing the overall well-being of the sub-region. (NAN)", "summary": "<img width=\"1080\" height=\"674\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2024/06/IMG-20240609-WA0003-e1717935202640.jpg?fit=1080%2C674&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" alt=\"President of the Senate, Godswill Akpabio and the Director-General of NILDS, Abubakar Sulaiman\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;max-width: 100%;\" link_thumbnail=\"\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2024/06/IMG-20240609-WA0003-e1717935202640.jpg?w=1080&amp;ssl=1 1080w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2024/06/IMG-20240609-WA0003-e1717935202640.jpg?resize=526%2C328&amp;ssl=1 526w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2024/06/IMG-20240609-WA0003-e1717935202640.jpg?resize=768%2C479&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2024/06/IMG-20240609-WA0003-e1717935202640.jpg?resize=150%2C94&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com", "url": "https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/more-news/702162-nilds-nigerians-no-longer-require-foreign-legislative-training-akpabio.html", "image": "https://media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2024/06/IMG-20240609-WA0003-e1717935202640.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 12:19:08", "author": "Agency Report,Femi Aribisala", "authors": ["Agency Report", "Femi Aribisala"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ng", "sentiment": -0.015}